text: Apha subdives is a moth in the family Eupterotidae. It was described by Francis Walker in 1855. It is found in Bangladesh, India, Bhutan, Myanmar, Thailand, Vietnam and China.BOLD Systems ==Subspecies== *Apha subdives subdives *Apha subdives honei Mell, 1937 *Apha subdives tychoona Butler, 1871 *Apha subdives yunnanensis Mell, 1937 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1855 Category:Eupterotinae
title: Apha subdives
